'''Dharmarāja Adhvarin''' (b. 17th century C.E., Khandaramanikkam, Tanjor, [[India]]) was a [[Hindu philosophy|Hindu philosopher]]. He developed the [[Advaita]] [[epistemology|theory of knowledge]]. Up to this point [[metaphysics]] and epistemology were treated as one in [[Indian philosophy]].<ref>''Great Thinkers of the Eastern World'', Ian McGreal</ref>
