'''Dongshan Shouchu''' ({{zh|t=洞山守初|w=Tung-shan Shou-ch'u}}; {{lang-ja|Tozan Shusho}}) (died 900) was a [[China|Chinese]] [[Zen]] teacher and an heir to [[Yunmen Wenyan]]. Dongshan is the subject of Case 18 "Three Pounds of Flax" in the [[Mumonkan]], a collection of [[koan]]s authored by [[Wumen|Mumon Ekai]] in 1228.
